FBIS3-32096 "drlat022_b_94009" FBIS-LAT-94-022 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Feb 1994 Inter-Caribbean Affairs Haiti Sen. Dupiton Said Linked to Izmery Assassination FL0102180194 Port-au-Prince Radio Tropic FM in French 1430 GMT 1 Feb 94 FL0102180194 Port-au-Prince Radio Tropic FM Language: French Article Type:BFN [Monitored in progress] [Text] ...December 1993 that the assassination of Antoine Izmery [Haitian businessman and Aristide supporter killed on 11 September 1993] was allegedly worked out meticulously at the home of former Senate President Thomas Eddy Dupiton, an out-and-out [Aristide] adversary close to Colonel Joseph Michel Francois. According to the weekly [JEUNE AFRIQUE], Senator Dupiton allegedly accommodated the killers the day before the crime. Ebrane Cadet, first secretary of the legitimate office of the Senate of the Republic, says in a letter to Colin Granderson, head of the international civilian mission, that he is alarmed about a document prepared by a special UN unit according to which Sen. Dupiton allegedly prepared the assassination of Antoine Izmery. Cadet asks Granderson for an explanation regarding this document.
